HGPRTase functions primarily to salvage purines from degraded DNA to reintroduce into purine synthetic pathways. In this role, it catalyzes the reaction between [[鳥嘌呤|guanine]] and [[磷酸核糖焦磷酸|phosphoribosyl pyrophosphate]] (PRPP) to form [[單磷酸鳥苷|GMP]], or between [[次黄嘌呤|hypoxanthine]] and [[磷酸核糖焦磷酸|phosphoribosyl pyrophosphate]] (PRPP) to form [[肌苷酸|inosine monophosphate]].
