== Hybridomas ==

{{tsl|en|Hybridoma||Hybridoma}}s are immortal (immune to {{tsl|en|cellular senescence||cellular senescence}}), HGPRT<sup>+</sup> cells that result from fusion of mortal, HGPRT<sup>+</sup> [[浆细胞|plasma cells]] and immortal, HGPRT<sup>−</sup> [[多發性骨髓瘤|myeloma]] cells. They are created to produce [[单克隆抗体|monoclonal antibodies]] in biotechnology. {{tsl|en|HAT medium||HAT medium}} inhibits [[从头合成|de novo synthesis]] of nucleic acids, killing myeloma cells that cannot switch over to the [[补救途径|salvage pathway]], due to lack of HRPT1. The plasma cells in the culture eventually die from senesence, leaving pure hybridoma cells.

